Titolo: TV Tennis Electrotennis

Anno: 1975

Descrizione: The TV Tennis Electrotennis (Japanese: テレビテニス, Hepburn romanzination: Terebitenisu, meaning Television Tennis, commonly abbreviated as TV Tennis or Electrotennis) is a dedicated first-generation home video game console that was released by Epoch Co. (developed in cooperation with Magnavox) on September 12, 1975 for 19,000 Japanese yen only in Japan. It was the first video game console ever released in Japan.It released several months before the release of Home Pong in North America. One unique feature of the TV Tennis Electrotennis is that the console is connected wirelessly to a TV, functioning through an UHF antenna. Depending on the source, it sold about 10,000, 20,000 or 3 million units in its lifetime, including about 5,000 units in the first year.

